  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "~I need to discuss something. `VoiceSearchHelper` is instantiated in `connectVoiceSearch`. The instance stores bunch of statuses. However the connector is called only once when creating VoiceSearch widget. It means if user puts VoiceSearch widget more than one on a same page, all the widgets will have same statuses. Is this correct?~\r\n~Having more than one VoiceSearch widget doesn't make any sense. And even if user does, the widgets cannot be used at the same time. Do we consider statuses being shared in several widgets as an issue? If so, the instantiation of the helper should be done in creation of the component. IMO, it's not an issue. What do you think? @Haroenv @francoischalifour~\r\n\r\nIgnore this. I was confused at the moment.",
    "created_at": "2019-04-08T09:34:59Z",
